Nexus API:
    - to get information that are needed in CI/CD
    - for ex. information of component, repository, versions etc.
    - It allows you to automate everything you normally do in the Nexus UI.

How to access REST endpoint?
    - using tool like curl or wget to execute http request 
    - request require user and password (use user with required permission)
    - it give json response

Query to see repository:
    curl -u user:password -X GET "http://143.110.243.95:8081/service/rest/v1/repositories"  
    - we can only see repository that are accessible to given user
    - if we give admin user and admin password we can see all

Query to see all the component in certain repository:
    - curl -u user:password -X GET "http://143.110.243.95:8081/service/rest/v1/components?repository=<REPO-NAME>"
    - curl -u user:password -X GET "http://143.110.243.95:8081/service/rest/v1/components?repository=maven-snapshots"

Query to see certain the component in certain repository:
    -  curl -u user:password -X GET "http://143.110.243.95:8081/service/rest/v1/components/<components_id>"